<p><a title="" name="_ftn3" href="#_ftnref3"> [3] </a> Phishing generally is an attempt to acquire sensitive information such as usernames, passwords, and credit card details by masquerading as a trustworthy entity in an electronic communication.</p>
<p><a title="" name="_ftn4" href="#_ftnref4"> [4] </a> <em>Malware</em> is a term used to refer to a variety of forms of hostile or intrusive software, including computer viruses, worms, Trojan horses, and other malicious programs that will infect the users computer with forms of executable code, scripts, active content, and other invasive software.</p>
<p><a title="" name="_ftn5" href="#_ftnref5"> [5] </a> Ransomware is a type of malware that demands a ransom payment in order to remove it from the infected computer.</p>
<p><a title="" name="_ftn6" href="#_ftnref6"> [6] </a> Dutch antispam law success, <a href="https://www.spamexperts.com/about/news/dutch-anti-spam-law-has-success">https://www.spamexperts.com/about/news/dutch-anti-spam-law-has-success</a>.</p>
